  <datafield tag="545" ind1="0" ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">Peter Pollack was a landscape architect who primarily worked in the Ann Arbor Area. He also taught at the University of Michigan School of Natural Resources.</subfield>
  </datafield>
  <datafield tag="520" ind1="2" ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">The Pollack collection consists of textual, visual, and digital materials. Project files make up the bulk of the collection. This includes correspondence, minutes, working files, project plans, and drawings documenting Pollack's involvement with various urban design and landscaping projects in the state of Michigan, in addition to his teaching career. Projects documented in the collection are grouped by Ann Arbor projects, Herman Miller projects, Pfizer campus projects, and Other Michigan projects. Ann Arbor projects include the Allen Creek Greenway Task Force, the Ann Arbor Corridor Study, the Farmer's Market Commission, the Parks, Recreation and Open Space Plan, Fuller Road, the State Street Pedestrian Project, and various projects related to the Downtown Development Authority. Other Michigan projects include Charlevoix Marina and Park, the Huron River Bikeway Study, the Huron-Whittaker Corridor Study, Independence Lake Park, and the Pere-Marquette Rail Trail.</subfield>
  </datafield>
  <datafield tag="506" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">The collection is open for research use.</subfield>
  </datafield>
